's revival. Diehl's analysis reveals how these atomic narratives shaped both the way Nagasaki rebuilt and the ways in which popular discourse on the atomic bombings framed the city's experience for decades.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Sep 2018) 0aAtomic bomb victimszJapanzNagasaki-shi. 0aCity planningzJapanzNagasaki-shixHistoryy20th century. 0aCollective memoryzJapanzNagasaki-shi. 0aReconstruction (1939-1951)zJapanzNagasaki-shi.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook-Package 2018z978311066747908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell Univ. Press eBook-Package Pilot Project 2018z978311060655308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2018 Englishz978311060403008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2018z9783110603149oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501709432423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501709432.jpg  a978-3-11-060403-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060655-3  Cornell Univ. Press eBook-Package Pilot Project 2018b2018  a978-3-11-064982-6  Asian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Package  a978-3-11-066747-9  COR eBook-Package 2018  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA